  "local_port": 39754,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do we forget any Wi-Fi in Windows 10?",
  "response": "Forgetting a Wi-Fi network in Windows 10 is relatively straightforward. Here are the steps:\n\n### Method 1: Using the Settings Menu\n\n1. **Open Settings**: Click the **Start menu** and select the **Settings** gear icon.\n   \n2. **Go to Network & Internet**: In the Settings menu, click on **Network & Internet**.\n\n3. **Navigate to Wi-Fi settings**: In the left-hand pane, click on **Wi-Fi**.\n\n4. **Manage known networks**: Click **Manage known networks**.\n\n5. **Select the network to forget**: Find the Wi-Fi network you want to forget in the list and click on it.\n\n6. **Forget the network**: Click on the **Forget** button that appears.\n\n### Method 2: Using Command Prompt\n\nIf you prefer using Command Prompt, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open Command Prompt**: \n   - Press **Win + X** to open the Power User menu.\n   - Click on **Command Prompt (Admin)** or **Windows PowerShell (Admin)**.\n\n2. **List all known Wi-Fi networks**:\n   - Type the following command: `netsh wlan show profiles`\n   - Press **Enter**. This will display all the Wi-Fi networks your computer remembers.\n\n3. **Forget the specific network**:\n   - Type the following command: `netsh wlan delete profile name=\"NETWORK_NAME\"`\n   - Replace **NETWORK_NAME** with the name of the Wi-Fi network you want to forget.\n   - Press **Enter**.\n\n### Method 3: Using Control Panel\n\nAlternatively, you can use Control Panel:\n\n1. **Open the Control Panel**:\n   - Type **Control Panel** in the search box on the taskbar and click on it.\n\n2. **Navigate to Network and Sharing Center**:\n   - Select **Network and Sharing Center**.\n\n3. **Manage wireless networks**:\n   - Look for **Manage wireless networks** on the left side. If it\u2019s not visible, you may have to enable it by changing the view settings to **Small icons** or **Large icons** in the top right corner.\n\n4. **Select and remove the network**:\n   - Find the network you want to forget, right-click on it, and select **Remove network**.\n\nBy following these steps using any of the methods above, you should be able to forget any Wi-Fi network on your Windows 10 computer.",
